- Become well-versed in the theoretical vocabulary of the field of religious studies;
- Deepen understanding of key theories, methods, concepts and issues in the academic study of religion;
- Reflect on the relationship between religion and the human condition;
- Engage in critical analysis of religious phenomena using the perspectives of key theories and methods in the academic study of religion;
- Develop a critical yet sympathetic attitude in discussing religious phenomena

Knowledge Outcomes:
- Upon completion of the subject, student will be able to
- Understand the establishment of knowledge of Religious Studies and research ethics;
- Learn the key writers on Religious Studies;
- Understand the key theories of Religious Studies in classical themes;
- Learn the major issues in the field of Religious Studies in contemporary scholarship;
- Develop the critical thinking on the debates regarding religious diversity, migration and religion, religious movement and so on.

