To become well-versed in theoretical and practical vocabulary of the field of Islamic Studies;
To deepen understanding of key theories, methods, concepts, and issues in the academic study of Islam;
To understand the history, scriptures, doctrines, and practices of the Islamic tradition;
Reading and analyzing primary source material from the Islamic tradition, including scriptures, legal, philosophical and mystical texts, etc.;
Reading and analyzing scholarly texts in the academic study of Islam;
Writing scholarly materials in genres appropriate to the field of the academic study of Islam, including research papers, exegetical essays, etc.
To develop a critical yet sympathetic attitude in discussing subjects in Islamic Studies.
